SYNOPSIS
========
   int write_file(string file, string str           )
   int write_file(string file, string str, int flags)

DESCRIPTION
===========
DESCRIPTION Append the string <str> to the file <file>. Returns 1 for success
and 0 if any failure occured.

If <flags> is 1, the file is removed first; thus making the 'append'
effectively an 'overwrite'. Default for <flags> is 0.

LDMud 3.3.523 added the <flags> parameter.

      See Also:
         file_size(E), write_bytes(E), write_file(E), read_file(E),

   read_bytes(E), rm(E), get_dir(E)
